// `napi::bindgen_prelude::*` brings `napi::Result` into scope as bare `Result`, but this
// module is written for String errors throughout (the non-napi build aliases `Result<T>`
// to `Result<T, String>` via `napi_stubs`). Shadow the prelude's `Result` back to the
// String-error form so the hundreds of internal `?` sites compile identically under both
// features; the `#[napi]` methods use the fully-qualified `napi::Result<T>` + map_err.
